import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['width', 'height']]
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='width', y='height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between the width and height of volcano eruptions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x=data['values'])
    plt.axvline(x=data['values'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['values'].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the average value of volcano eruptions?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
